# Tree math test vectors

The tree math functions are defined in the annex of the [protocol](https://github.com/mlswg/mls-protocol/blob/master/draft-ietf-mls-protocol.md)

The test vectors are calculated in the following way:

```
size = 255;
range = [0, 254];

for i in range
{
	test_vector.add(tree_function(i, size));
}
```

The test vectors are encoded in the following format: 

Functions that return an integer

```
struct {
	uint8 x<0..255>;
} vector;
```

Functions that return an array of integers

```
struct {
	vector y<0..255>;
} vector2d;
```
